minimalFix:
To fix the issue, the `NotificationPlugin`'s event handler must dynamically read the latest configuration values from `this.configLoader` every time it processes an event. This ensures that even if the configuration changes after the plugin's initialization, the handler always uses the most current `maxRetries` and `logLevel`.

```typescript
// src/plugins/NotificationPlugin.ts
export class NotificationPlugin {
  // ... other properties and constructor

  init(): void {
    // Config values should be dynamically read within the handler,
    // not captured at init time.
    const handler = (event: DataEvent) => {
      const { logLevel, maxRetries } = this.configLoader.getConfig(); // Dynamically get latest config

      const result: ProcessedResult = {
        source: event.source,
        processed: true,
        retries: maxRetries, // Now uses latest maxRetries
        logLevel: logLevel,   // Now uses latest logLevel
      };

      if (logLevel !== 'silent') { // Now uses latest logLevel
        console.log(`[NotificationPlugin] Processing event from ${event.source}`);
      }

      this.results.push(result);
    };

    this.bus.on<DataEvent>('data:received', handler);
  }

  // ... other methods
}
```
